    <div class="col-12">
      <p class="p2-wwd">
        <span style="background-color: red">We neither are looking for the so-called 'truth'</span>
        nor do we intend to make a prediction of the future. Dharma does want to find common knowledge,
        or what agents believe other agents consider to be the so-called 'truth'.
      </p>
      <p class="p2-wwd">Dharma exists to answer two questions:</p>
      <p class="p3-wwd"><span style="background-color: red">When do narratives change and what is already 'priced in'?</span></p>
      <p class="p3-wwd"><span style="background-color: red">Who said what and why?</span></p>
    </div>
  </div>
  <div class="row inactive-tab text-center"  id='tab-3'>
    <div class="col-12">
      <h2 class='h2-wwd pb-3'>
        It turns out that...
      </h2>
      <p class='p2-wwd'>
        Given all possible <span style="background-color: red">NARRATIVES</span> out there, which one should <span style="background-color: red">WE MONITOR</span>?
